Spicy Guava and Habanero Rum Sauce

3 tbsp olive oil
1 lb yellow onion, roughyl chopped
6 oz (3/4 c) guava paste
1 1/4 c water
1/3 c sriracha
5 tbsp dark rum
2 1/2 tbsp lemon juice
2 tbsp tomato paste
5 tsp light brown sugar
2 1/2 tsp apple cider vinegar
1/4 tsp ground allspice
1/8 tsp curry powder
1 star anise
1/2 habanero pepper, stemmed and seeded
kosher salt to taste

In a medium saucepan, heat the oil over medium high heat. Add the onions and cook until soft and light brown around the edges, 8min. Add the remaining ingredients, except the habanero and salt, then bring to a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally until slightly thickened, 12-15 min. Remove from the heat and transfer to a blender with the habanero. Puree until smooth, then season with salt. allow to cool completely before using. Can store in refrigerator up to 1 week.
